# <type>(optional scope): <subject>
# <BLANK LINE>
# [optional body]
# <BLANK LINE>
# [optional footer(s)]

# type
#    feat: :sparkles: A new feature
#    fix: :bug: A bug fix
#    refactor: :wrench: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#    perf: :zap: A code change that improves performance
#    test:  :white_check_mark: Adding missing or correcting existing tests
#    docs: :memo: Documentation only changes
#    style: :lipstick: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
#    build: :building_construction: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#    ci: :construction_worker: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
#    chore: :pencil2: Other changes that don't modify source or test files
#    revert: :rewind: Reverts a previous commit
#    security: :lock: Security to invite users to upgrade in case of vulnerabilities
#    deps: :arrow_up:/:arrow_down: Dependencies upgrading or downgrading
#    i18n:  Internationalization and localization
#    config: Configuration changes

# optional scope: Explain what part of the codebase is changed
#   - could be a module, feature, component e.g
#   - (login),(controllers/navbar),(models)

# subject: Short summary
#   - Do not end with a period
#   - Not cased
#   - Start writing in lowercase
#   - 100 characters or less
#   - Use the imperative mood(add user login feature, update README, refactor login)

# optional body: Explain why this change is being made.
#   - Wrap it to about 100 characters or so
#   - Can use multiple lines with "-" for bullet points
#   - Explain what and why vs. how

# optional footer(s): Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets
#   - Wrap it to about 100 characters or so
#   - Linking a pull request to an issue using a keyword
#     - close #ISSUE-NUMBER
#     - fix #ISSUE-NUMBER
#     - resolve #ISSUE-NUMBER

# --------------------
# Conventional Commits
# A specification for adding human and machine-readable meaning to commit messages
# Ref: https://www.conventionalcommits.org
# --------------------
